title: Winter Storms, United States by County, 2000-2007
name: Winter Storms, United States by County, 2000-2007
description:
This information was found by searching for reports of winter weather by all states and all counties at SHELDUS. SHELDUS is a county-level data set for the U.S. on 18 different natural hazard event types along with property and crop losses, injuries, and fatalities for the period January 1960 through December 2007. The database was compiled to examine spatial and temporal variability in historical hazard events and associated losses.U.S. county boundaries are adjusted to 2000 designations.

A pivot table was used to get a total count for occurrences of winter weather by county and state and represents sums of information for those occurrences.  Event and Loss Data Sources: The data were derived from several existing national data sources, of which National Climatic Data Center's monthly Storm Data publications are the major data source. 

The county and states were geocoded for latitude and longitude at batchgeocode.com and gpsvisualizer.com. The data was uploaded into Geocommons as a csv.

author.source: SHELDUS, Spatial Hazards Events and Losses Database for the United States
